tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control, while current blood glucose is slightly low, possibly due to recent hypoglycemic episodes or treatment. Renal function, electrolytes, and other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend review of diabetes management to prevent hypoglycemia and improve overall glycemic control.
